OL,3,CPolice boss praises officers' conduct
OL,4,Cbefore shooting of armed knifeman
OL,6,FThe court was told that the officer,
OL,7,Fwhose identity is protected by an
OL,8,Fanonymity order and was referred to as
OL,9,FOfficer A, fired the gun between 18
OL,10,Fand 22 seconds after he entered the
OL,11,Fcar park with another armed officer,
OL,12,Fcalled Officer B.
OL,14,FThe officer said he told Mr Ciolac to
OL,15,Fdrop the knife, but did not say he was
OL,16,F"armed police", before he ran at him
OL,17,Fwith the weapon raised.
OL,19,F"The situation that was faced that day
OL,20,Fwas unprecedented"
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/17
