OL,3,CPolice boss praises officers' conduct
OL,4,Cbefore shooting of armed knifeman
OL,6,FIndependent Office for Police Conduct
OL,7,F(IOPC) Director Derrick Campbell said:
OL,8,F"Our thoughts remain with Marius
OL,9,FCiolac's family and everyone affected
OL,10,Fby his death.
OL,12,F"Fatal police shootings are
OL,13,Ffortunately rare and lethal force must
OL,14,Fonly be used by officers when
OL,15,Fabsolutely necessary.
OL,17,F"When such incidents happen, it's
OL,18,Fvital that the circumstances
OL,19,Fsurrounding the shooting are
OL,20,Fthoroughly and independently examined.
OL,26,@pD@AOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G14/17
