OL,3,CPolice boss praises officers' conduct
OL,4,Cbefore shooting of armed knifeman
OL,6,F"Based on the available evidence, we
OL,7,Ffound that the decision to shoot Mr
OL,8,FCiolac was reasonable in the
OL,9,Fcircumstances."
OL,11,FThe IPOC added "We found no indication
OL,12,Fthat any officers should face
OL,13,Fdisciplinary action or had committed a
OL,14,Fcriminal offence.
OL,16,F"All the police officers involved were
OL,17,Ftreated as witnesses throughout our
OL,18,Fenquiries."
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@OO]
